This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with scene graph generation from images. It also involves attentional mechanisms and neural networks, which are common topics in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as it deals with generating textual descriptions of scenes. Finally, the use of graph neural networks suggests that the paper may also belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
